metadata.name: Catrina 2658
metadata.description:
A pleasant and intense aroma of cempasuchil flowers transports her through the universe, vibrating at a high frequency, teleporting between planets and dimensions until she reaches the land of tacos and agaves. A pair of intergalactic birds are her companions on this journey, witnessing the glow of cosmic dust emanating from her heart.

The year is already 2658, and a voice is still being heard in La Condesa (in front of Parque México, to be exact) that says: “se compran, colchones, tambores, refrigeradores, estufas, lavadoras, micro ondas; o ¿algo de fierro viejo que vendan?...
